a, Croatia, and Serbia, and also among Rusyns (in Serbia and Croatia). See also   Pop   2 and   Popa  .","English: variant of   Pape   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Papp","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]},{"name":"Jenkin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal names <i>Jankin</i>, <i>Jenkin</i>, and <i>Jonkin</i>, pet forms of <i>Jan</i>, <i>Jen</i>, and <i>Jon</i> + the hypocoristic suffix <i>-kin</i>. In Middle English, names in <i>-kin</i> were often used to name the younger of two family members with the same personal name."],"variants":[{"name":"Jenkins","meanings":["English and Welsh: variant of   Jenkin  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. <i>Jenkins</i> is one of the most common surnames in England, especially southwestern England, but is also especially associated with Wales."]},{"name":"Jenks","meanings":["English (West Midlands): from the Middle English personal name <i>Jenke</i> (a shortening of the personal name <i>Jenkin</i>, <i>Jankin</i>; see   Jenkin  ), with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","History: Joseph Jenks (1602–83), the descendant of an old Welsh family, was born in England and traveled to Saugus, near Lynn, MA, in 1642 to assist in the development of America's first iron works. His son, Joseph Jenckes (sic), followed in 1650, founded Pawtucket, RI, and raised four sons who held places of respect and distinction in RI, including one who served as governor for five years."]},{"name":"Jenkinson","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): from the Middle English personal names <i>Jankin</i>, <i>Jenkin</i>, or <i>Jonkin</i> (see   Jenkin  ) + <i>son</i>."]}]},{"name":"Dafydd","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>David</b> . In widespread use during the Middle Ages, it was later largely replaced by the English form, but since the late 19th century it has come into its own again."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Wr","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese: variant of   Wei  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Wei","meanings":["‘Impressive might’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Dafydd Wr ap Jenkin was born about 1334, in Glamorgan, Wales. She had at least 1 son with Dafydd \" Wr\" ap Jenkin."},"et":{"about 1334–":"umbes 1334–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1334–Female":"1334–Surnud","about 1370":"umbes 1370","1334":"1334","about 1334":"umbes 1334","1330":"1330","1370":"1370","Aberavon, Glamorgan, Wales":"Aberavon, Glamorgan, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1334–":"noin 1334–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","1334–Female":"1334–Kuollut","about 1370":"noin 1370","1334":"1334","about 1334":"noin 1334","1330":"1330","1370":"1370","Aberavon, Glamorgan, Wales":"Aberavon, Glamorgan, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1334–":"environ 1334–Décédée","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1370–Male":"1370–Décédé","1334–Female":"1334–Décédée","about 1370":"environ 1370","1334":"1334","about 1334":"environ 1334","1330":"1330","1370":"1370","Aberavon, Glamorgan, Wales":"Aberavon, Glamorgan, Galles","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Galles","lifeSumma